messages.message:
@Venkatesh said I should post this here. Please let me know if it should go to a different channel.

We are working with https://aihub.instabasedev.com and was working with the `Process Files` step. Processing a file is resulting in `"lines": null` for some reason. I have attached a screenshot of this result, along with the Process Files OCR Config Settings. Please let me know if you need additional information. The location of the flow is `hopping-cow/chul.gwon.ctr_instabase.com/fs/Instabase (http://ctr_instabase.com/fs/Instabase) Drive/doc_tagging/csg_test_2.ibflow`
cc: @Balaram! Since Vasu is OOO! Can you pls assign someone to look into this?
In IBDOC v2 we don't store the lines information in the master ibdoc, we store it in the shards. But in a UDF if you want to read the lines that should not be a problem.
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1SBBjzMHPwdNiWIjbka3LrS5aNOHplFZPPl6NPnxdueU/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.5gzsxpf39s4k - let us know whether this is helpful for accessing the lines data
Hey @Atinder. Enable ibdoc_v2 was on by default. What are the implications of turning this off? The use is very simple. Classification and extraction at a high level
ibdoc_v2 is memory efficient and helps with faster processing of longer documents. Are you planning to use it for a demo? @Venkatesh
